value.title: Scalise not ready to accept Biden win: 'Let the legal process play out'
value.excerpt: House Minority Whip Steve Scalise, R-La., said he will continue supporting efforts challenging the election results even as the Electoral College is set to officially elect Joe Biden as the next president on Monday.

value.title: Trump: Coronavirus vaccine would have taken 'five years' if I wasn't president
value.excerpt: President Trump said finding a coronavirus vaccine would have taken "five years" if he weren't president during an interview that aired Sunday.

value.title: Trump tells 'Fox & Friends' election challenges 'not over' ahead of Electoral College vote
value.excerpt: President Trump vowed that he and his campaign “are going to continue to go forward” with their legal challenges against November’s election results, despite the Electoral College getting set to cast their votes on Monday.

value.title: Flashback: Biden praised ‘constant,' 'unrelenting’ stream of immigration into US
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden, during the Obama administration, said the U.S. benefits from a “constant” and “unrelenting” stream of immigration -- and that those with white European heritage becoming a minority in the U.S. is "a source of our strength."

value.title: Trump says Barr 'a big disappointment' after report AG knew about Hunter Biden investigation months ago
value.excerpt: President Trump on Saturday described Attorney General William Barr as a “big disappointment” after a report claiming the nation’s top lawyer knew about the Hunter Biden investigation months ago.

value.title: Jordan claims Trump 'paid what he owed' in response to NY Times report
value.excerpt: One poll says nearly three in four registered voters plan to tune in to see President Trump face off against Democratic nominee Joe Biden tonight.  MACCALLUM: Fireworks are anticipated as theshowdown comes against a tense backdrop in thenation.

value.title: Hunter Biden requested keys for new 'office mates' Joe Biden, Chinese 'emissary' to CEFC chairman, emails show
value.excerpt: Hunter Biden requested in 2017 that keys be made for his new "office mates," listing his father, President-elect Joe Biden, Jill Biden and his uncle, Jim Biden, for space he planned to share with an "emissary" for a chairman of a Chinese energy company, according to an email obtained by Fox News.

value.title: Mike Pompeo, Mike Pence go to bat for imprisoned Hong Kong media tycoon Jimmy Lai

value.title: Rep. Jim Jordan: Voters not knowing about Hunter Biden probe before election 'is just wrong'
value.excerpt: The media and the American people should have known about the federal investigation into President-elect Joe Biden's son Hunter prior to last month's presidential election, Rep. Jim Jordan, R-Ohio, said on Friday.

value.title: Fox News Poll: Most Republicans say President Trump was robbed
value.excerpt: Sixty-eight percent of Republicans believe the election was stolen from President Trump, according to the latest Fox News national survey of registered voters.

value.title: Black Lives Matter accuses Biden of ignoring them: 'It's demeaning to our hurt and trauma'
value.excerpt: Black Lives Matter accused President-elect Joe Biden of ignoring their request for a meeting and disregarding the Black voters that helped secure his White House victory.

value.title: CNN's Harwood: Republicans would 'smack their moms in the face' to please Donald Trump
value.excerpt: CNN White House correspondent John Harwood said Friday that Republican members of Congress would hit their own mothers if President Trump wanted.

value.title: MSNBC's Maddow: I've learned from Trump era not to blindly trust government officials

value.title: US-China tensions worsen with Hunter Biden, Eric Swalwell revelations: GOP lawmakers
value.excerpt: The clouds over Hunter Biden, whose business dealings in China were investigated by two GOP committee chairs in the Senate, and Rep. Eric Swalwell, D-Calif., raise fresh questions about how the United States will confront one of its top strategic foes in 2021 and beyond.

value.title: Whitmer says Michigan GOP went ‘too far’ against anti-Trump state Democrat
value.excerpt: Michigan state Republicans went “too far” in saying they would pull committee assignments from a state Democrat who threatened Trump supporters in a viral video, the state’s Democratic governor said Thursday.

value.title: AOC knocks Joe Biden’s agenda as ‘a little hazy’
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden has started to fill out key roles in his cabinet and staff before he takes office, but Congresswoman Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez, D-N.Y., said this week that she'd like to see a more unified unit.

value.title: Ari Fleischer: Mainstream media committed 'dereliction of duty' by not reporting on Hunter Biden
value.excerpt: "The press was derelict in its duty" by not following up on the New York Post's reporting about Hunter Biden's overseas business dealings, former White House Press Secretary Ari Fleischer told “Outnumbered Overtime” on Thursday.

value.title: Biden's pick of Denis McDonough for VA sparks pushback from veterans
value.excerpt: The aftermath of President-elect Joe Biden’s pick for secretary of Veteran Affairs has been met with responses of “surprise” after long-time Obama aide Denis McDonough was selected to be only the second non-veteran to take up the seat Thursday.

value.title: Pence says Trump ‘deserves his day’ in Supreme Court
value.excerpt: Saying “God bless Texas,” Vice President Mike Pence on Thursday gave a rousing endorsement of a lawsuit filed by the Texas attorney general and backed by President Trump that aims to throw out the election results in four key battleground states won last month by President-elect Donald Trump.

value.title: Kamala Harris’s husband will teach at Georgetown Law school
value.excerpt: Vice President-elect Kamala Harris’ husband Douglas Emhoff will join the staff of Georgetown University’s law school next month. Emhoff, 56, will be the first non-female and first Jewish ...

value.title: Biden, in leaked audio, suggests GOP 'beat the living h--- out of us' over 'defund the police'
value.excerpt: Biden said that public calls for police reform should be avoided ahead of the Georgia Senate runoff vote.

value.title: Ilhan Omar 'quite happy' with Biden officials' receptiveness to her ideas
value.excerpt: “Squad” member Rep. Ilhan Omar, D-Minn., said she was “quite happy” with the response after submitting a list of proposed left-wing executive actions at a meeting with President-elect Joe Biden’s transition team.

value.title: Biden further slims Democratic House majority with USDA pick, despite worries from some top Democrats
value.excerpt: With House Democrats down to their slimmest majority in the chamber since World War II, a former chief of staff to House Speaker Nancy Pelosi is warning President-elect Joe Biden and his team to stop grabbing congressional Democrats for his incoming administration.

value.title: Morocco normalizing ties with Israel, 4th country to do so under Trump's Arab peace plan
value.excerpt: Morocco will normalize relations with Israel, making it the fourth country to do so in recent days under a U.S.-brokered deal.

value.title: Grassley claims media 'chose to dismiss' Hunter Biden probe: 'I think it's outrageous'
value.excerpt: Sen. Chuck Grassley, R-Iowa, accused the "liberal media" of ignoring his investigation of the Biden family's finances in order to protect the Democratic Party while speaking on the Senate floor on Thursday.

value.title: Pence announces first two Space Force bases in US
value.excerpt: The renaming is ahead of a mission realignment, which should happen following a congressional briefing.

value.title: Chris Rock calls on Joe Biden to create 'Supreme Court of Science' to handle any crisis like the coronavirus
value.excerpt: Chris Rock called on President-elect Joe Biden to institute a fourth branch of government dedicated to science in order to combat another crisis like the coronavirus pandemic in a bipartisan way.

value.title: Trump administration names China, Nigeria, Iran to list of countries lacking religious freedom
value.excerpt: The Trump administration on Monday named China, Nigeria and Iran to the list of countries that engage in violating or allowing violations of religious freedom within their borders — part of U.S. efforts to end religious persecution around the world.

value.title: Obama says Trump did 'serious damage' to policy accomplishments but ACA 'remains robust'
